    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWe have internal shims for luajit features:\n\n```\nrequire('string.buffer')\nrequire('table.clear')\nrequire('table.new')\n```\n\nref https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39222\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDocument and expose these for use by plugins.\nAssuming there is no risk of forward incompatibility.\n\nNote\n\n- Lua 5.5 has a `table.create`, which is similar to `require('table.new')`, but still lacks `require('table.clear')`",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> We have plans to add other things there too such as table.pack\n\nMy vote would go towards putting these things under the `vim` namespace instead of monkey patching `table`. For people switching between Neovim luadev and other Lua projects, it's confusing if Lua stdlib components have methods that aren't part of Lua5.1 or LuaJit. ",
